  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam Australia Extractives Tax Report Project Support in Serra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">OXFAM in Sierra Leone with support from Oxfam Australia (OAU) and ODK seeks to take these findings and recommendations relevant to Sierra Leone and lead the local level advocacy. The well -functioning of modern society is effectively based on the good and fast circulation of information.  Main Objectives of OXFAM Sierra Leone in Public Awareness Activities and Advocacy on this study include:  i. Develop sustained programmes of public information (electronic, printed, audio, audio -visual) and institutionalized educational components pertaining to findings and recommendations of the report to prevent tax avoidance and Inequality using the Inequality Platform at Regional, National and Local levels (MAISL).  ii. Influence Improve criteria through a multi prong approach to pressure Iluka via International Finance Corporation (IFC) &#x2022; Sub Objective: Putting pressure on the IFC to do better due diligence on responsible tax before investing in projects (a promise that was made in 2016 when they stated in this update that they would &quot;review the overall terms of the investment, including the overall economic and fiscal contribution to the host country&quot;) &#x2022; Sub Objective : Use the IFC to put pressure on Iluka and the Government of Sierra Leone to negotiate for better fiscal terms. &#x2022; Sub objective : Use the IFC involvement to get more publicity for the report and to raise awareness among donors and others of the pitfalls of private sector support. &#x2022; Sub Objective : IFC to work with Sierra Rutile Limited to increase its positive impact on local communities</narrative>
  </description>
